review_blob:
Beautiful nose...wonderful flavor...Any day with Westvleteren Abt 12 a good day!  

I look forward to winter just so I ca drink wonderful beers like these.
Sextuple?  Is that a double triple? Trancendent beer.  I cannot get information from anywhere about future batches.  Still have 7-8 bottles, but have to hoard them until I get more information.

With the upcoming release of the 2009 Behemoth, I felt it would be nice to retaste the 2008.  It has evolved beautifully.  While some of the over-the-top hoppiness upon release has dropped out.  The hop/malt balance is extraordinary.

beer_brewer_name: Port Brewing Co / The Lost Abbey
review_blob: I was stunned...The alcohol, at 10%, was not overstated.  The hop character was perfectly balanced in both aroma and on the palette.  I feel fortunate to have been able to experience this...A great DIPA.

Probably my favorite annual offering.  Had a mini vertical 2007-2008.  Both were different but extremely delicious. Perfection in a glass.  Dark chocolate, caramel with wrapped in a beautiful robe of bourbon.  A truly inspired beer...Also recently had the Blueberry Bourbon County Stout at the brewpub...Mind expanding!
It had been a few years since I last had this beer.  Shared one with some friends...It did not disappoint.  Beautiful nose with the perfect melding of the cherries.  Wonderful
